# Implementation Plan - Fix Movement Oscillation

## Problem
Character oscillates left/right around the rope entry point.
Log: `Pos=(63) Target=(59)`. Moves Left -> `Pos=(57)`. Moves Right -> `Pos=(61)`.
This happens because:
1. [MoveToTargetAsync](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Services/CharacterMovementController.cs#200-329) tolerance is **1.0px**.
2. Minimum move step (Tap) is **~4.0px** (due to 120ms duration).
3. The character continually overshoots the 1px target.

## Solution
Increase the horizontal alignment tolerance in [MoveToTargetAsync](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Services/CharacterMovementController.cs#200-329).
Set it to **5.0px**.
This effectively creates a "parking zone". If the character is within 5px (e.g., at 63px vs 59px), it considers itself "Aligned" and stops moving.
The logic then hands over to [MainForm](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/UI/MainForm_MinimapControl.cs#5-42), which checks if `distance < 10px`. Since `4px < 10px`, it proceeds to [ClimbRopeAsync](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Services/CharacterMovementController.cs#641-884).

## Proposed Changes

### Services/CharacterMovementController.cs

#### [MODIFY] MoveToTargetAsync
- **Tolerance Check**:
  ```csharp
  // Increase from 1.0 > 5.0 to prevent oscillation
  if (Math.Abs(dx) > 5.0) 
  {
      // Move Left/Right
  }
  else
  {
     // Aligned
  }
  ```

## Verification Plan
- **Scenario**: Character approaches rope at X=59 from X=63.
- **Result**: Character sees `dx=4`. `4 < 5`. Stops moving. Logs "Aligned".
- **Transition**: [MainForm](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/UI/MainForm_MinimapControl.cs#5-42) sees `dist=4 < 10`. Calls [ClimbRopeAsync](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Services/CharacterMovementController.cs#641-884). Character climbs.
